    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "I want to acknowledge the CTO's perspective -- Wang Hao's technical skills are genuine, and losing a strong engineer is a real cost.\n\nHowever, there's an important nuance in Huang Lei's assessment that should be highlighted: Huang Lei said Wang Hao's technical skills are strong -- but he specifically recommended **P6 senior IC**, not P7 team lead. The CTO is citing Huang Lei's technical praise while not addressing Huang Lei's level recommendation.\n\n**The actual Huang Lei recommendation:**\n- Technical skills: P6-level solid (confirmed)\n- Leadership experience: Inflated (confirmed by interview observation)\n- Hire recommendation: P6 senior IC, NOT P7 team lead\n- Condition: Candidate must be honest about the discrepancies\n\nThe question is not \"hire vs don't hire\" -- it's \"hire at what level and with what disclosure.\" A P6 offer based on verified skills is very different from a P7 offer based on unverified resume claims.\n\nZhang Wei (HR VP) has also weighed in supporting the evidence-based approach. Would you like to see the full background check report?"
        }
      ],
      "timestamp": 1773828720000,
      "__openclaw": {
